  "text": "Zulkarnain and Leviäkangas [CITATION_1] also argued that stronger manufacturing and system providers within the ITS industry would signal greater industrial potential for Finland. Even with the current trend of industry servitization, the roles of traditional equipment and hardware providers are crucial because the integration of the value chain occurs mostly from upstream to downstream. In other words, the hardware and equipment manufacturers move downstream to provide services, not vice versa. Unless there is a strong equipment and hardware manufacturing base in the country, there will be fewer opportunities to create a domestic service sector to come alongside manufacturing.",
